- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the traffic patterns of various applications that use content-type requests, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the formulation of content-type requests, which can be seen as a data structure. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper mentions search engines and recommender networks, which are applications related to information retrieval. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper mentions newsfeeds and advertisement networks, which are applications related to social and information networks.
